{"html":"<p></p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 707px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Google Flights being awesome\" title=\"Google Flights being awesome\" src=\"/static/4a7c4bd5cda1ecbeadd23bdff902fbf2/3bf56/dica-amiga.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/4a7c4bd5cda1ecbeadd23bdff902fbf2/db830/dica-amiga.jpg 256w,\n/static/4a7c4bd5cda1ecbeadd23bdff902fbf2/8102f/dica-amiga.jpg 512w,\n/static/4a7c4bd5cda1ecbeadd23bdff902fbf2/3bf56/dica-amiga.jpg 707w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 707px) 100vw, 707px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\">\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Google Flights being awesome</figcaption>\n  </figure><p></p>\n<p>Well, recently I found out that Google had created the wonderful Google Flights, which is a search engine for flights from various airlines, like how Skyscanner does. The most amazing thing is that this site has been around for years, and I only discovered it this week, despite having traveled a lot and always looking for cheap tickets, I had never heard about Google Flights.</p>\n<p>And the cool thing is that if you are planning a trip and have a way to lower the price of your ticket by changing a few days on the way and / or return, Google Flights suggests this to you. It’s fast, useful and doesn’t charge fees, well, what else can I say? Since then I’m sure I’ll only use Google Flights for all my searches, so here’s the tip for you :)</p>","path":"/en/blog/tips/google-flights-op/","title":"Google Flights OP","language":"en","postHashId":"dGlwc3RydWUuLi8uLi9jb3ZlcnMvMjAxNS9wb3N0LWlkLTIyODQtY292ZXIucG5nMjAxNS0wNS0zMVQwMDowMDowMC4wMDBa","comments":[],"relatedPosts":[{"path":"/en/blog/events/trip-to-la-e3-2014/","postHashId":"ZXZlbnRzdHJ1ZS4uLy4uL2NvdmVycy8yMDE0L3Bvc3QtaWQtMjI2Ni1jb3Zlci5wbmcyMDE0LTA4LTA4VDAwOjAwOjAwLjAwMFo=","title":"Trip to LA - E3 2014","date":"2014-08-08T00:00:00.000Z"},{"path":"/en/blog/toys/lego-love/","postHashId":"dG95c3RydWUuLi8uLi9jb3ZlcnMvMjAxMy9wb3N0LWlkLTIyNDMtY292ZXIucG5nMjAxMy0wMi0wOVQwMDowMDowMC4wMDBa","title":"Lego love","date":"2013-02-09T00:00:00.000Z"},{"path":"/en/blog/events/trip-to-e3-2012/","postHashId":"ZXZlbnRzdHJ1ZS4uLy4uL2NvdmVycy8yMDEyL3Bvc3QtaWQtMjIzMy1jb3Zlci5wbmcyMDEyLTEyLTIwVDAwOjAwOjAwLjAwMFo=","title":"Trip to E3 2012","date":"2012-12-20T00:00:00.000Z"},{"path":"/en/blog/events/e3-2012-and-here-we-go/","postHashId":"ZXZlbnRzdHJ1ZS4uLy4uL2NvdmVycy8yMDEyL3Bvc3QtaWQtMjIyMS1jb3Zlci5wbmcyMDEyLTA1LTMxVDAwOjAwOjAwLjAwMFo=","title":"E3 2012 - And here we... Go","date":"2012-05-31T00:00:00.000Z"},{"path":"/en/blog/tips/unboxing-white-chocolate-easter-egg/","postHashId":"dGlwc3RydWUuLi8uLi9jb3ZlcnMvMjAxMC9wb3N0LWlkLTIwMDMtY292ZXIucG5nMjAxMC0wNC0wN1QwMDowMDowMC4wMDBa","title":"Unboxing white chocolate easter egg","date":"2010-04-07T00:00:00.000Z"},{"path":"/en/blog/games/creating-my-dream-skyward-sword-hd-switch-accessories/","postHashId":"Z2FtZXN0cnVlbnVsbDIwMjEtMDctMTRUMDA6MDA6MDAuMDAwWg==","title":"Creating my dream Skyward Sword HD Switch accessories","date":"2021-07-14T00:00:00.000Z"},{"path":"/en/blog/general/an-open-letter-to-mark-manson/","postHashId":"Z2VuZXJhbHRydWUuLi8uLi9jb3ZlcnMvMjAxNi9wb3N0LWlkLTIyOTctY292ZXIucG5nMjAxNi0wMi0xNlQwMDowMDowMC4wMDBa","title":"An open letter to Mark Manson","date":"2016-02-16T00:00:00.000Z"},{"path":"/en/blog/games/new-handheld-revo-k101-gba-clone/","postHashId":"Z2FtZXN0cnVlLi4vLi4vY292ZXJzLzIwMTMvcG9zdC1pZC0yMjM4LWNvdmVyLnBuZzIwMTMtMDItMDlUMDA6MDA6MDAuMDAwWg==","title":"New handheld: Revo K101 (GBA clon